text: Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. It may be difficult to remember that not so long ago, Brie Larson wasn't yet a household name. That all changed when she took on the role of Carol Danvers, aka Captain Marvel, in the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU). The film, which was released in March 2019, was a massive success, grossing over $1.1 billion worldwide Captain Marvel's abilities are rooted in her genetic makeup and Kree physiology. She has superhuman strength, speed, agility, durability, and reflexes. She also possesses enhanced senses, including vision and hearing. Her body is capable of absorbing and processing immense amounts of energy, making her highly resistant to injury Captain Marvel is a superhero film directed by Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck. The movie is based on the character of Carol Danvers from the Marvel Comics series. The film stars Brie Larson, Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, Djimon Hounsou, Lee Pace, Lashana Lynch, Gemma Chan, Annette Bening, Clark Gregg, and Jude Law The latest news, rumors, and updates about Captain Marvel, starring Brie Larson as Carol Danvers/Captain Marvel, with Jude Law as Yon-Rogg, and Ben Mendelsohn as Talos/Kree spy.
